We write JS files for NetSuite, and as such have an api file we include in our projects to provide some intellisense. This works in other IDEs:

Small snipet from api file:

```js
/**
 * Return a new instance of nlobjRequest used for scripting web requests in Suitelets
 *
 * @classDescription Accessor to Http request data made available to Suitelets
 * @return {nlobjRequest}
 * @constructor
 */
function nlobjRequest( ) { return new nlobjRequest(); }

/**
 * return the value of a request parameter.
 *
 * @param {string} name parameter name
 * @return {string}
 * @method
 * @memberOf nlobjRequest
 *
 * @since 2008.2
 */
nlobjRequest.prototype.getParameter = function( name ) { return new String(); }
```

In our actual script, the parameter types remain as 'any'

```js
